ξ 1 1. seu, ‘ or else ;' ‘ and we would rather believe that he did not leave Ardea until he learnt that the law was passed.' The senate could only pass a ‘ consultum' authorising or recommending this course; and since the Roman ‘populus’ was now at V eii, the Comitia Curiata would be held there and the lex passed.

mutari finibus, ‘he could not be removed in point of territory (in domicile),’ i. e. into Roman territory.

lex curiata, generally used of the lex curiata de imperio, see note on 1. 1 : here of a law reinstating Camillus. Weissenborn suggests that it was passed by the Curiae because he had to be reinstated in his Gens: but Livy is not a good authority on the Comitia.
